The paper deals with building high-level features from unlabeled data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The authors use a deep neural network for unsupervised learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the recognition of object categories, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
